          <div class="accordion-usage-grid">
            <div>
              <p class="doc-tabs__panel-copy accordion-usage-label" data-i18n="components.accordion.design.doH3">✅ Do</p>
              <ul class="accordion-usage-list">
              <li data-i18n="components.accordion.design.do1">Use accordion for grouped, optional, or progressive content.</li>
              <li data-i18n="components.accordion.design.do2">Write labels that help users predict what expands.</li>
              <li data-i18n="components.accordion.design.do3">Keep chevron placement consistent within the same set.</li>
              <li data-i18n="components.accordion.design.do4">
                Start rows collapsed by default unless expanded content is immediately required.
              </li>
              <li data-i18n="components.accordion.design.do5">
                Use dividers and spacing consistently in stacked groups.
              </li>
              <li data-i18n="components.accordion.design.do6">
                When using leading icons, apply them consistently across all rows in the same set.
              </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="doc-tabs__panel-copy accordion-usage-label" data-i18n="components.accordion.design.dontH3">🚫 Don&apos;t</p>
              <ul class="accordion-usage-list">
              <li data-i18n="components.accordion.design.dont1">Hide critical information users need immediately.</li>
              <li data-i18n="components.accordion.design.dont2">
                Mix leading and trailing chevrons in one set without a strong reason.
              </li>
              <li data-i18n="components.accordion.design.dont3">
                Use vague labels such as &quot;More&quot; or &quot;Details&quot; without context.
              </li>
              <li data-i18n="components.accordion.design.dont4">Overload a single row with too many optional elements.</li>
              <li data-i18n="components.accordion.design.dont5">
                Let expanded content feel disconnected from its triggering row.
              </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
